  </entry>
  <entry>
    <id>https://community.sap.com/t5/enterprise-resource-planning-q-a/unexpected-journal-entry-appearing-in-tax-report-with-incorrect-taxable/qaq-p/14056172</id>
    <title>Unexpected Journal Entry Appearing in Tax Report with Incorrect Taxable Amounts</title>
    <updated>2025-03-25T16:19:39.797000+01:00</updated>
    <author>
      <name>Y-Yusuf</name>
      <uri>https://community.sap.com/t5/user/viewprofilepage/user-id/1448637</uri>
    </author>
    <content>&lt;P&gt;We encountered an issue in SAP Business One where a journal entry (JE) related to an internal fund transfer (reclassification entry) appears in the tax report, even though it contains no tax-related transactions. Additionally, the taxable amount and tax values in the report do not match the original JE details.&lt;/P&gt;&lt;P&gt;For example, the JE records a 29,900 TRY transfer between accounts, but the tax report incorrectly displays 1,250 TRY taxable amount and 250 TRY tax, which disrupts the tax declaration.&lt;/P&gt;</content>
